00024 bool ORIgorFileReader::ReadRecord(UInt_t*& buffer, size_t& nLongsMax)
00025 {
00026   // First, read in the header if necessary.
00027   if(fStreamVersion == ORHeaderDecoder::kUnknownVersion) {
00028     /* We increment the run number to make sure that files don.t
00029      * get overwritten.  This is because the file name is taken
00030      * from the run number in the header. */
00031     fRunNumber++;
00032     std::string header = ReadHeader();
00033     UInt_t nBytes = header.size() + 1;
00034     UInt_t recordLength = ((UInt_t) ceil(double(nBytes)/4.0)) + 2;
00035     if(nLongsMax < recordLength) {
00036       nLongsMax = DeleteAndResizeBuffer(buffer, recordLength);
00037     }
00038     buffer[0] = recordLength;
00039     buffer[1] = nBytes;
00040     memcpy(buffer+2, header.c_str(), nBytes);
00041     /* Here we assume that the igor files come from a little endian (PC) 
00042        machine. */
00043     fStreamVersion = ORHeaderDecoder::kOld;
00044     if(ORUtils::SysIsLittleEndian()) {
00045       fMustSwap = false;
00046     } else {
00047       fMustSwap = true;
00048     }
00049     return true;
00050   }
00051 
00052   ORBasicDataDecoder decoder;
00053   UInt_t theBuffSizeLong = 0;
00054   if(Read(((char*) &theBuffSizeLong), 4) != 4) return false; // XIA specific, we grab the first 32-bits
00055   if(MustSwap()) ORUtils::Swap(theBuffSizeLong);
00056   UShort_t theBuffSize = (theBuffSizeLong & 0x0000FFFF);
00057   
00058   // the first 32-bits on an Orca file gives the length of the buffer dump
00059   // in 32-bit words.  plugging in the appropriate values.
00060   // also the dataID of the DGF.
00061   buffer[0] = theBuffSize/2 + theBuffSize % 2 + 2;  
00062   buffer[0] += 262144; // this is the correct dataID for the DGF  
00063   // the second 32-bits has Crate ID, etc.  this is unimportant
00064   buffer[1] = 0x00000000; // set second 32 bits to 0
00065   // the 3rd 32-bits takes the 1st 32 bits read out and the rest of the
00066   // stream is just shifted by 64 bits.
00067   if(MustSwap()) ORUtils::Swap(theBuffSizeLong);
00068   // We need to swap back since the swapping of the record is not handled
00069   // here
00070   buffer[2] = theBuffSizeLong;
00071 
00072   if (!OKToRead()) return false;
00073   size_t longRecordLength = theBuffSize/2 + 2 + theBuffSize % 2;  
00074   // we're adding 2 longs to the buffer
00075   if (longRecordLength > nLongsMax) {
00076     UInt_t tmp = buffer[0];
00077     UInt_t tmp1 = buffer[1];
00078     UInt_t tmp2 = buffer[2];
00079     nLongsMax = DeleteAndResizeBuffer(buffer, longRecordLength);
00080     buffer[0] = tmp;
00081     buffer[1] = tmp1;
00082     buffer[2] = tmp2;
00083   }
00084   size_t nBytesToRead = (theBuffSize-2)*2;  // XIA is 16 bit.
00085   size_t nBytesRead = Read(((char*) buffer)+12, nBytesToRead);
00086   if (nBytesRead != nBytesToRead) {
00087     ORLog(kWarning) << "ReadRecord(): attempt to read " << nBytesToRead
00088                     << " B only returned " << nBytesRead << "B "
00089               << "(id = " << decoder.DataIdOf(buffer) << ", "
00090               << "len = " << longRecordLength << ")" << std::endl;
00091     return false;
00092   }
00093   return OKToRead();
00094 }
